Load and parse .gitignore files (or any list of pattern strings using the same pattern syntax) to produce an IgnoreList, which can be used to ignore specific files and folders during (for example) a file copy operation.
The goal of this library is to implement the same file matching behaviour which Git uses to determine which files to ignore when adding to a commit. Please feel free to submit issues with examples or pull requests if you find instances where this isn't the case!

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
CustomerService InsertPricelistItem now allows update of PriceRecommended
ProductService: Product.ImageKey gets set from variant's ImageKey if one exists, otherwise ImageKey is taken from Product. [Review this! Probably we should take product, when populating product and use this approach when populatin variants.] Product.Files now have a new property, Extension, that can be used to construct correct url to the image. Just append Extension to the ImageKey when dealing with images ocr files. CategorItem now have a new property, Synonym, that can be used to index categories by synonyms. A new method, ListWarehouseInfo, for listing all available warehouses/locations and stores have been added.
ShoppingService: Fix in Klarna Checkout when handling ship-to address. Fix in error handling in the payment process. Now correct FaultName is included in the Exception. PaymentMethods can now be configured to only be valid for specific categories. I.e all items in the basket must be from configured categories for the payment method to be valid.
Promotions: Fix of price calculations when using fixed discount. Now the amount is calculated correctly.
General: Minor changes in cache eviction policy.
Major changes internally in how products are fetched in order to get better performance. Behavior should be as before.

FeedPackage.Description: Enferno Storm API Client library.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
OrderService: Added support for application specific data on Order, DeliveryNote and Invoice.
- New Collection, InfoList, used to keep application specific data on Order, DeliveryNote and Invoice. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Orders/Collections
- New Property, Info, on Order, DeliveryNote and Invoice. See InfoList above. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Orders/Entities/DeliveryNote https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Orders/Entities/Invoice https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Orders/Entities/Order
- New Entity, Info. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Orders/Entities/Info
ProductService: Minor additions on Product and ProductItem
- New Property, IsSubscribable, on Product and ProductItem. Used for Subscriptions, see ShoppingService below. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Entities/Product https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Entities/ProductItem
ShoppingService: Now supporting creation of recurring orders with the use of Subscriptions. Not 100% completed yet. One minor addition to Promotion.
- New Collections, SheduleList, SubscriptionList and SubscriptionTypeList. Used for Subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Collections
- New Property, IsSubscribable on BasketItem. Can be used to see if a BasketItem can be copied to a Subscription. Not fully implemented.
- New Entity, Subscription. Defines a Subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/Subscription
- New Entity, SubscriptionSchedule. Defines a schedule for a Subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionSchedule
- New Entity, SubscriptionSheduleData. General data for scheduling Subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionScheduleData
- New Entity, SubscriptionType. A SubscriptionType specified for the application. Used by Subscription. SubscriptionTypes are created in StormAdmin. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionType
- New Method, CreateSubscription. Used to create subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/CreateSubscription
- New Method, GetSubscription. Used to get a subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/GetSubscription
- New Method, GetSubscriptionScheduleData. Used to get meta data for scheduling subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/GetSubscriptionScheduleData
- New Method, ListSubscriptions. Used to list active and old Subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptions
- New Method, ListSubscriptionStatus. Used to list available status ids for Subscriptions. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptionStatus
- New Method, ListSubscriptionTypes. Used to list all available SubscriptionTypes. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptionTypes
- New Method, PurchaseSubscription. Used to buy a Subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/PurchaseSubscription
- New Method, UpdateSubscription. Used to update data on a Subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/UpdateSubscription
- New Method, DeleteSubscription. Used to delete an active subscription. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/DeleteSubscription

ShoppingService: #9359: Now supporting creation of recurring orders with the use of Subscriptions. Not 100% completed yet. #9306: One minor addition to Promotion.
- New Collections, SheduleList, SubscriptionList and SubscriptionTypeList. Used for Subscriptions. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Collections

- New Entity, SubscriptionSchedule. Defines a schedule for a Subscription. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionSchedule
- New Entity, SubscriptionSheduleData. General data for scheduling Subscriptions. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionScheduleData
- New Entity, SubscriptionType. A SubscriptionType specified for the application. Used by Subscription. SubscriptionTypes are created in StormAdmin. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/SubscriptionType
- New Method, CreateSubscription. Used to create subscriptions. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/CreateSubscription
- New Method, GetSubscription. Used to get a subscription. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/GetSubscription
- New Method, GetSubscriptionScheduleData. Used to get meta data for scheduling subscriptions. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/GetSubscriptionScheduleData
- New Method, ListSubscriptions. Used to list active and old Subscriptions. Not fully implemented and subject to change. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptions
- New Method, ListSubscriptionStatus. Used to list available status ids for Subscriptions. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptionStatus
- New Method, ListSubscriptionTypes. Used to list all available SubscriptionTypes. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptionTypes
- New Method, PurchaseSubscription. Used to buy a Subscription. Not fully implemented and subject to change. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/PurchaseSubscription
- New Method, UpdateSubscription. Used to update data on a Subscription. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/UpdateSubscription
- New Method, DeleteSubscription. Used to delete an active subscription. https://services.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/DeleteSubscription
- #9306: Promotion Effect, Discount Products, now supports discounting the most expensive products. Can only be used when restricting usage with Quantity.
What's fixed? - ListIncludedProducts: Now returns correct price and part no from StructureItems.
- #9385: ProductFlags are now sorted according to sort order from StormAdmin.
- #9307: Fix in Checkout when changing company on Buyer, Payer or ShipTo for customers with more than one company.
- #9603: Extended length of ProductName on BasketItem to be same as for Products.
- #9654: ListProducts now returns True|False as value in ProductItem.ParametricValueSeed. Previously 0|1 was returned. This is to have same behavior as for Product.
Miscellaneous changes? ApplicationService: - Rewrites of ListApplicationFlags, ListApplicationFlagGroups, ListInfoTypes, ListStores, ListStoreItems, GetStoreItem, GetStoreItemByUniqueName, GetStoreItemByCountryAndZipCode, GetStore, GetStoreByUniqueName, ListStores2, UpdateDivisionInfo. Internal code improvements.
ShoppingService: - Internal code improvements in CreateBasket, InsertBasketItem. - Added validation on InsertBasketItem. Closed products cannot be inserted. Will throw a “Bad Request”.
General: - Minor additions to online documentation.
- Restricted number of parallel processes when handling batched calls to 15.
- Localized all error messages returned for Bad Requests and added a property Messages on exception Detail that is a dictionary of fault codes and messages. Now deprecating the NameValues XML used previously. Localized languages codes are de, de, en, es, et, fi, fr, it, lt, lv, nl, no, sv. Most of them are google translated so corrections are appreciated. Default is en.
Feedback? Faults and strange behavior can be reported to support@enferno.se or to patrik.rosquist@enferno.se.
Regards, The Storm API Team

FeedPackage.Description: Enferno Storm API Client library.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
What's new? ShoppingService: - New Property, DescriptionHeader on BasketItem. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Entities/BasketItem
- Changed Method, ListSubscriptions. Added parameters to enable filtering on status. Although this is a breaking change it will not impact any client sites since this is new functionality not used yet. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListSubscriptions
- New Method, UpdateBasket2. Replaces UpdateBasket (Depricated) since UpdateBasket had some side effects on customer data which was not intended. UpdateBasket2 updates basket data excluding any customer data. To change customer data on a Basket use UpdateBuyer/UpdatePayer/UpdateShipTo. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/UpdateBasket2
What's fixed? ShoppingService: - ShipTo Customer data such as name, phone and email was not saved correctly and defaulted to the Buyer's data. This has now been fixed in the API but still needs changes in the order workflow and StormAdmin. This also applies to KlarnaCheckout when payments have been accepted. Impact is in all methods handling customer data on Basket.
Promotions: #9622: UsageCount on Promotions with discount codes and usage limit was not working correctly. This has now been fixed.
Miscellaneous changes? ShoppingService: - Internal code improvements in almost all methods in ShoppingService. Added more reuse of cached products when populating BasketItems. This impacts all methods that change BasketItems.
Feedback? Faults and strange behavior can be reported to support@enferno.se or to patrik.rosquist@enferno.se.
Regards, The Storm API Team

What's new?
CustomerService: - #10132 A new method, GetCustomerByCode has been added. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Customers/Operations/GetCustomerByCode
- #10100 Flags have now been added to Company and PricelistIds have been added to Customer. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Customers/Entities/Company https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Customers/Entities/Customer
ProductService: - #9958 IsBuyable has been added to ProductPrice and is false if the product is closed or if the sku itself is not buyable.
ShoppingService: - # 10112 A new property, IsPriceManual, on BasketItem. Used when setting price on BasketItem with UpdateBasketItem or when using InsertBasketItem. When setting prices, set BasketItem.Price to the correct price and BasketItem.IsPriceManual to true. To revert to the original price just set IsPriceManual = false.
What's fixed?
ProductService: - #9958 IsBuyable on ProductItem/Product now behaves equally and is now false if the product is closed. Previously it was only false if the product had IsBuyable = false. Products with IsBuyable = true that are closed will show as not buyable.
ShoppingService: - #9958 IsBuyable on BasketItem is now false if the product is closed. Previously it was only false if the product had IsBuyable = false. Products with IsBuyable = true that are closed will show as not buyable.
- #10007 The reservation logic for OnHand in the Checkout now ignores products of type virtual, except when the virtual product is a structure item. Then the reservation is made on the included items.
- #10110 Problem with promotions with multiple effects where the effects matched more than one basketitem has now been fixed. Previously just the first effect was applied.
Miscellaneous changes?
ShoppingService: - #10007 The reservation logic for OnHand in the Checkout now ignores products of type virtual, except when the virtual product is a structure item. Then the reservation is made on the included items.
Feedback? Faults and strange behavior can be reported to support@enferno.se or to patrik.rosquist@enferno.se.
Regards, The Storm API Team

ShoppingService: - #9958 IsBuyable on BasketItem is now false if the product is closed. Previously it was only false if the product had IsBuyable = false. Products with IsBuyable = true that are closed will show as not buyable.
- #9778 The reservation logic for OnHand in the Checkout now ignores products of type virtual, except when the virtual product is a structure item. Then the reservation is made on the included items.
- #10110 Problem with promotions with multiple effects where the effects matched more than one basketitem has now been fixed. Previously just the first effect was applied.
Miscellaneous changes?
OrderService: - #10310 Caching of orderlists has been removed. Ity is now up to the application to cache the list when appropriate.
ShoppingService: - #10007 The reservation logic for OnHand in the Checkout now ignores products of type virtual, except when the virtual product is a structure item. Then the reservation is made on the included items.
- Some remaining problems with addresses on Checkout has been resolved. This partly affected ShipTo addresses.
Feedback? Faults and strange behavior can be reported to support@enferno.se or to patrik.rosquist@enferno.se.
Regards, The Storm API Team

FeedPackage.Description: Enferno Storm Commerce API Client library.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
What's new?
ApplicationService: - # 409 We now support applications without any public pricelists. This gives that all calls to methods with pricelistSeed must supply a valid pricelistSeed, or no Products will be fetched. If the application have valid pricelists then pricelistSeed is optional as before. See 1069 below.
ProductService, ShoppingService: - # 1069 pricelistSeed is now used to filter any valid pricelists. If none is supplied all valid pricelists for applications will be used.
ProductService: - #408: Two methods, ListOnHandInfoByPartNo and ListOnHandInfoByProduct, have been added. These add support for having custom info flields on OnHand for warehouse/locations. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Operations/ListOnHandInfoByPartNo https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Operations/ListOnHandInfoByProduct These return a list of OnHandInfo. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Entities/OnHandInfo
ShoppingService: - #408: One method, ListOnHandInfoByBasket has been added. It adds support for having custom info fields on OnHand for warehouse/locations. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Shopping/Operations/ListOnHandInfoByBasket It returns a list of OnHandInfo. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Products/Entities/OnHandInfo
ExposeService: - #406 A new method, ListErrorMessages, lista all available Name/Values for all Bad Requests raised by the API. Later on a list of Exceptions will be provided in the documentation for each method. https://servicesstage.enferno.se/api/1.1/docs/#/Expose%20(Empty)/Operations/ListErrorMessages
What's fixed?
ShoppingService: - #410 The creation of our internal OrderRequest, which is used in the payment and order process has been moved to the API from our internal order process. This affects payments and orders, and should improve performance in the checkout process since we now skip remote calls.
- # 1016 Support for different currencies on Baskets. Previously basket's currency was defaulted to the Application's default currency and used in payments and on order. Now the basket's currency can be set in CreateBasket, by setting Basket.CurrencyId or Basket.CurrencyCode to appropriate values in the supplied basket. If nothing is specified, the default will be used as before. The basket will then be handled in that currency for payments and order. This should not affect existing applications using only the default currency.
- #1013 DeleteBasket now verifies that only normal baskets (Type = 1) can be deleted. Deleted baskets will not be available through the API and handled as missing and null will be returned when trying to get a deleted basket.
Miscellaneous changes?
General: - Improvements in the documentation.
Feedback? Faults and strange behavior can be reported to support@storm.io or to patrik.rosquist@storm.io.
Regards, The Storm API Team
